## 2. Fluxo OAuth2 (Per User)

```
Utilizador clica "Ligar Google Calendar"
  │
  ▼
GET /api/auth/google
  → Gera state token (CSRF protection)
  → Guarda state em cookie httpOnly
  → Redirect para:
    https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/v2/auth
      ?client_id=XXX
      &redirect_uri=XXX
      &response_type=code
      &scope=https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar
      &access_type=offline        ← IMPORTANTE: pede refresh_token
      &prompt=consent              ← Força consent para garantir refresh_token
      &state=CSRF_TOKEN
  │
  ▼
Google mostra ecrã de consentimento
  → Utilizador autoriza
  │
  ▼
Google redirect para /api/auth/google/callback?code=XXX&state=XXX
  │
  ├─ Validar state vs cookie
  ├─ Trocar code por tokens:
  │    POST https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token
  │      grant_type=authorization_code
  │      code=XXX
  │      client_id=XXX
  │      client_secret=XXX
  │      redirect_uri=XXX
  │    → Recebe: access_token, refresh_token, expires_in
  │
  ├─ Encriptar tokens (AES-256-GCM)
  ├─ Guardar em temp_user_google_tokens
  ├─ Fazer sync inicial (últimos 30 dias)
  │
  └─ Redirect para /dashboard/definicoes com toast "Google Calendar ligado"
```

### Refresh do Access Token

O access_token expira em ~1 hora. Antes de cada chamada à API:

```typescript
async function getValidAccessToken(userId: string): Promise<string> {
  const tokenRecord = await getGoogleTokens(userId)
  if (!tokenRecord) throw new Error('Google Calendar não ligado')

  // Se ainda válido, usar
  if (new Date(tokenRecord.expires_at) > new Date(Date.now() + 60000)) {
    return decrypt(tokenRecord.access_token)
  }

  // Senão, refresh
  const res = await fetch('https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' },
    body: new URLSearchParams({
      grant_type: 'refresh_token',
      refresh_token: decrypt(tokenRecord.refresh_token),
      client_id: process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID!,
      client_secret: process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET!,
    }),
  })

  const data = await res.json()
  // Actualizar tokens na DB
  await updateGoogleTokens(userId, {
    access_token: encrypt(data.access_token),
    expires_at: new Date(Date.now() + data.expires_in * 1000).toISOString(),
  })

  return data.access_token
}
```

